* --------------------------------------------------- *
* This is a sample member that demonstrates using the *
* documentation popup statements.                     *
*                                                     *
* Use the command RUNC -ALL to see how this works.    *
*                                                     *
* --------------------------------------------------- *

* First the TSO Status command
ST

* Now some documentation for a popup
<DOC>
<title>First Doc Pop-Up
After viewing the instructions in the pop-up the following
commands will be issued:

Display XCF      To display the current XCF members
Dispaly SMF      To display the current SMF datasets

Pressing Enter will not close the pop-up.

PF3 will close the pop-up and continue to the next commands.

Entering CANCEL in the command field will close the popup and
exit further RUNC processing.
</DOC>
cons d xcf
cons d smf
<doc>
<title>A few more examples
This documentation popup demonstates all the supported symbolics:

The symbolics used are:

   USA Date (mm/dd/yy)                &&DATE      &DATE
   2 digit Day of Month               &&DD        &DD
   Day of year (e.g. 001)             &&DOY       &DOY
   European Date (dd/mm/yy)           &&EDATE     &EDATE
   Hours and Minutes                  &&HHMM      &HHMM
   Julian Date (e.g. 16001)           &&JDATE     &JDATE
   Julian Date                        &&JULIAN    &JULIAN
   Active LPAR Name                   &&LPAR      &LPAR
   2 digit Month                      &&MM        &MM
   Month (e.g. January)               &&MONTH     &MONTH
   Ordered Date (yy/mm/dd)            &&ODATE     &ODATE
   Current TSO Prefix                 &&PREFIX    &PREFIX
   Current dataset                    &&RDSN      &RDSN
   Current member                     &&RMBR      &RMBR
   Current member                     &&RMEM      &RMEM
   Standard Date (yyyymmdd)           &&SDATE     &SDATE
   Active SMFID for the LPAR          &&SMFID     &SMFID
   Active LPAR Name                   &&SYSNAME   &SYSNAME
   1 Character System Name            &&SYSID     &SYSID
   Active SYSPLEX Name                &&SYSPLEX   &SYSPLEX
   Current TSO Prefix                 &&SYSPREF   &SYSPREF
   Active SMFID for the LPAR          &&SYSSMFID  &SYSSMFID
   Current userid                     &&SYSUID    &SYSUID
   USA Date (mm/dd/yy)                &&UDATE     &UDATE
   Current userid                     &&USERID    &USERID
   Current userid lower case          &&USERIDL   &USERIDL
   Day of Week (e.g. Monday)          &&WEEKDAY   &WEEKDAY
   2 digit Year                       &&YY        &YY
   4 digit Year                       &&YYYY      &YYYY
</doc>
